1;s:9:"Erik Hess";}s:6:"topics";a:5:{i:0;s:7:"anxiety";i:1;s:4:"fear";i:2;s:4:"risk";i:3;s:3:"iOS";i:4;s:7:"Android";}s:6:"banner";s:0:"";s:7:"caption";s:0:"";s:8:"download";s:67:"http://www.buzzsprout.com/7417/103144-043-anxiety-fear-and-risk.mp3";s:6:"player";s:164:"<iframe width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/116772748"></iframe>";s:7:"summary";s:449:"This week Gabe and Erik talk about things that make them anxious, the difference between anxiety and fear, and ways they assess and manage risk so they can be functioning members of society. Then they veer off topic to examine the possibility that iOS 7's new look might siphon development resources away from new and improved app features. Finally, they throw all caution to the wind to talk about Erik's brief dip in the foreign waters of Android.";s:7:"content";s:4:"true";s:11:"content_raw";s:4:"true";s:5:"_file";s:86:"/Users/erik/Dropbox/dev/td/_content/1-episodes/2013-07-15-043-anxiety-fear-and-risk.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:51:"/1-episodes/2013-07-15-043-anxiety-fear-and-risk.md";s:10:"_order_key";i:1373860800;s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";i:1373860800;s:4:"date";s:15:"July 15th, 2013";s:4:"time";N;s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1383345267;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:7:"_folder";s:8:"episodes";s:4:"slug";s:25:"043-anxiety-fear-and-risk";s:9:"_basename";s:39:"2013-07-15-043-anxiety-fear-and-risk.md";s:9:"_filename";s:36:"2013-07-15-043-anxiety-fear-and-risk";s:9:"_is_entry";i:1;s:8:"_is_page";i:0;s:3:"url";s:35:"/episodes/043-anxiety-fear-and-risk";s:9:"permalink";s:66:"http://technicaldifficulties.us/episodes/043-anxiety-fear-and-risk";}s:59:"/1-episodes/2013-07-23-044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith.md";a:31:{s:6:"number";s:3:"044";s:5:"title";s:29:"Facing Email with Eddie Smith";s:4:"type";a:1:{i:0;s:10:"discussion";}s:6:"people";a:3:{i:0;s:16:"Gabe Weatherhead";i:1;s:9:"Erik Hess";i:2;s:11:"Eddie Smith";}s:6:"topics";a:3:{i:0;s:5:"email";i:1;s:12:"productivity";i:2;s:4:"TEDx";}s:6:"banner";s:0:"";s:7:"caption";s:0:"";s:8:"download";s:75:"http://www.buzzsprout.com/7417/104559-044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith.mp3";s:6:"player";s:164:"<iframe width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/116770494"></iframe>";s:7:"summary";s:474:"Gabe and Erik are joined by Eddie Smith of Practically Efficient to talk about email. With dozens of competing messaging services, why do we still use email? How should we organize it? In the era of social networking, what are people's cultural expectations around how email is used? What barriers does email present to good communication, and how do we overcome those barriers to make email useful? This week's session of Generational Offtopic looks Eddie's work with TEDx.";s:7:"content";s:4:"true";s:11:"content_raw";s:4:"true";s:5:"_file";s:94:"/Users/erik/Dropbox/dev/td/_content/1-episodes/2013-07-23-044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:59:"/1-episodes/2013-07-23-044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith.md";s:10:"_order_key";i:1374552000;s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";i:1374552000;s:4:"date";s:15:"July 23rd, 2013";s:4:"time";N;s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1383345281;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:7:"_folder";s:8:"episodes";s:4:"slug";s:33:"044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith";s:9:"_basename";s:47:"2013-07-23-044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith.md";s:9:"_filename";s:44:"2013-07-23-044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith";s:9:"_is_entry";i:1;s:8:"_is_page";i:0;s:3:"url";s:43:"/episodes/044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith";s:9:"permalink";s:74:"http://technicaldifficulties.us/episodes/044-facing-email-with-eddie-smith";}s:75:"/1-episodes/2013-07-01-041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger.md";a:31:{s:6:"number";s:3:"041";s:5:"title";s:45:"The Death and Life of RSS with Alex Kessinger";s:4:"type";a:1:{i:0;s:9:"interview";}s:6:"people";a:3:{i:0;s:16:"Gabe Weatherhead";i:1;s:9:"Erik Hess";i:2;s:14:"Alex Kessinger";}s:6:"topics";a:3:{i:0;s:3:"RSS";i:1;s:7:"App.net";i:2;s:7:"Privacy";}s:6:"banner";s:0:"";s:7:"caption";s:0:"";s:8:"download";s:91:"http://www.buzzsprout.com/7417/100894-041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger.mp3";s:6:"player";s:164:"<iframe width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/116839878"></iframe>";s:7:"summary";s:520:"To celebrate the demise of Google Reader, Erik and Gabe talk to Alex Kessinger of Rumproarious. They discuss the RSS apocalypse, current Google Reader alternatives, ways to manage high volume feeds, and the future of the RSS landscape. Alex is a developer at App.net, so they also touch on a few notable apps that build on its growing social platform. This week also features the debut of a new section: Offtopic. The first offtopic... er, topic... is whether online privacy can still exist on the post-Snowden internet.";s:7:"content";s:4:"true";s:11:"content_raw";s:4:"true";s:5:"_file";s:110:"/Users/erik/Dropbox/dev/td/_content/1-episodes/2013-07-01-041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:75:"/1-episodes/2013-07-01-041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger.md";s:10:"_order_key";i:1372651200;s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";i:1372651200;s:4:"date";s:14:"July 1st, 2013";s:4:"time";N;s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1383345251;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:7:"_folder";s:8:"episodes";s:4:"slug";s:49:"041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger";s:9:"_basename";s:63:"2013-07-01-041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger.md";s:9:"_filename";s:60:"2013-07-01-041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger";s:9:"_is_entry";i:1;s:8:"_is_page";i:0;s:3:"url";s:59:"/episodes/041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger";s:9:"permalink";s:90:"http://technicaldifficulties.us/episodes/041-the-death-and-life-of-rss-with-alex-kessinger";}s:87:"/1-episodes/2013-06-24-040-helping-erik-procrastinate-productively-with-a-gtd-reboot.md";a:31:{s:6:"number";s:3:"040";s:5:"title";s:57:"Helping Erik Procrastinate Productively with a GTD Reboot";s:4:"type";a:1:{i:0;s:10:"discussion";}s:6:"people";a:2:{i:0;s:16:"Gabe Weatherhead";i:1;s:9:"Erik Hess";}s:6:"topics";a:5:{i:0;s:3:"GTD";i:1;s:12:"productivity";i:2;s:9:"OmniFocus";i:3;s:9:"Reminders";i:4;s:8:"Evernote";}s:6:"banner";s:11:"barrier.jpg";s:7:"caption";s:55:"An F8F takes the barrier on USS Tarawa (CV-40) in 1948.";s:8:"download";s:102:"http://www.buzzsprout.com/7417/99593-040-helping-erik-procrastinate-productively-with-a-gtd-reboot.mp3";s:6:"player";s:164:"<iframe width="100%" height="166" scrolling="no" frameborder="no" src="https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/116840610"></iframe>";s:7:"summary";s:444:"It's all come crashing down in Erik's work life, so Gabe helps Erik rethink his system for Getting Things Done. Along the way, they share their different perspectives and talk about how they handle multiple family members and multiple areas of responsibility. Finally, Gabe and Erik dig into a few major apps, hierarchy, tags, start dates and all sorts of other fiddly productivity topics that are a whole lot more interesting than actual work.";s:7:"content";s:4:"true";s:11:"content_raw";s:4:"true";s:5:"_file";s:122:"/Users/erik/Dropbox/dev/td/_content/1-episodes/2013-06-24-040-helping-erik-procrastinate-productively-with-a-gtd-reboot.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:87:"/1-episodes/2013-06-24-040-helping-erik-procrastinate-productively-with-a-gtd-reboot.md";s:10:"_order_key";i:1372046400;s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";i:1372046400;s:4:"date";s:15:"June 24th, 2013";s:4:"time";N;s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1382621124;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:7:"_folder";s:8:"episodes";s:4:"slug";s:61:"040-helping-erik-procrastina